<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Benefits
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	You will be eligible to participate in all of the employee benefits and benefit plans that the Company generally makes available to its full-time regular employees, subject to the terms and conditions of such benefits and benefit plans.&nbsp;&nbsp;At this time, these will include at a minimum, medical, dental and vision insurance coverage. Coverage for these benefits begins on the 1
<SUP STYLE="FONT-SIZE:85%; VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
	st
</SUP>
	day of the month following your date of hire. Detailed information about the benefits presently available will be provided to you on your first day of employment.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The health plan options will include 4 medical plans (2-HMO, PPO and HSA), a dental and vision plan, life/AD&amp;D insurance, disability and voluntary insurance as well as a 401(k) retirement plan.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company will cover 90% of the employee benefit costs and 75% of the dependent benefits costs.&nbsp;&nbsp;Based on conditions and situations over time, the Company may change specific benefits and plans from time to time, but our intent is to provide an excellent health benefit program to our employees.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	You will be entitled to accrue and use vacation time at the rate of 160 hours per year, up to an accrual cap of 240 hours, in accordance with the terms of the Company&#8217;s time off policy. In addition, you will also be eligible for 5 sick days.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	&#8220;At Will&#8221; Employment
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Employment with the Company is &#8220;at-will&#8221;.&nbsp;&nbsp;This means that it is not for any specified period of time and can be terminated by you or by the Company at any time, with or without advance notice, and for any or no particular reason or Cause.&nbsp;&nbsp;It also means that your job duties, title, responsibilities, reporting level, compensation and benefits, as well as the Company&#8217;s personnel policies and procedures, may be changed at any time, with or without notice in the sole discretion of the Company.&nbsp;&nbsp;This &#8220;at-will&#8221; nature of your employment shall remain unchanged during your tenure as an employee, and can only be changed by an express written agreement that is signed by you and by the Company&#8217;s CEO.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>

<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; WIDTH:100%;">

<TD STYLE="WIDTH:49.72%;">
</TD>

<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#9BBB59;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	www.ultragenyx.com
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#7F7F7F;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	3
</P>
</TD>
</TR>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">

<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage127"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="RARE-EX1036_615_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU4">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Severance
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	If, at any time, your employment with the Company or its successor is terminated without Cause, or you resign your employment due to a Constructive Termination, then provided such termination constitutes a Separation from Service, the Company shall: (i) extend the exercise period applicable to the Option (and to any other options to purchase the Company&#8217;s Common Stock you then hold) such that you will have until the date that is twelve (12) months after the date of your Separation from Service to exercise any of the vested shares (determined as of the date of your Separation from Service) subject to the Option (but in no event will the exercise period be extended until later than the date of expiration of the term of the Option as set forth in the agreement evidencing such Option); and (ii) the Company shall pay you, as severance the equivalent of one (1) year of your Base Salary in effect as of the date of your Separation from Service, subject to standard payroll deductions and withholdings (the &#8220;Severance Amount&#8221;).&nbsp;&nbsp;The Severance Amount will be paid in installments in the form of continuation of your Base Salary payments, paid on the Company&#8217;s regular payroll dates, commencing on the Company&#8217;s first regular payroll date that follows the 60th day after such Separation from Service.&nbsp;&nbsp;The first regular payroll date that follows the 60
<SUP STYLE="FONT-SIZE:85%; VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
	th
</SUP>
	day after such Separation from Service shall be for all accrued Base Salary for the 60-day period plus the period from the 60
<SUP STYLE="FONT-SIZE:85%; VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
	th
</SUP>
	day until the regular payroll date; the remainder of the Base Salary continuation payments shall thereafter be made on the Company&#8217;s regular payroll dates.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Notwithstanding anything herein to the contrary, the receipt of any of the severance or acceleration benefits described in this letter will be subject to and conditioned upon: (i) your signing a separation agreement and release of claims in a form reasonably satisfactory to the Company (the &#8220;Separation Agreement&#8221;) and such Separation Agreement becoming effective and irrevocable as specified therein no later than sixty (60) days following your Separation from Service; and (ii) your continued compliance with the terms of this letter, the Separation Agreement, the enclosed Confidential Information and Invention Assignment Agreement (including without limitation, your not using or disclosing any confidential or proprietary information of the Company), and any other agreement entered into between you and the Company.&nbsp;&nbsp;No severance benefits of any kind will be paid or provided, and no acceleration of vesting shall be effective, until the Separation Agreement becomes effective.&nbsp;&nbsp;You shall also resign from all positions and terminate any relationships as an employee, advisor, officer or director with the Company and any of its affiliates, each effective on the date of termination.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Additionally, and for the avoidance of doubt, in the event that the Company terminates your employment for Cause, or you resign your employment for any reason other than due to a Constructive Termination, or your employment terminates upon your death or disability, you will no longer vest in the Option or the RSUs (or any other equity) and you will not be entitled to any severance benefits described herein.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;

	www.ultragenyx.com
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#7F7F7F;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">

<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage128"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="RARE-EX1036_615_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU5">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	For purposes of this offer letter, &#8220;Cause&#8221; means any of the following: (i) your gross negligence in carrying out, or material failure to carry out, your duties for the Company (including without limitation, your failure to cooperate in any Company investigation), after notice from the Board and a reasonable opportunity to cure (if deemed curable); (ii) any breach of your fiduciary duties to the Company, after notice from the Board and a reasonable opportunity to cure (if deemed curable); (iii) conviction of, or plea of guilty or no contest to, any felony; (iv) any act of fraud or embezzlement by you with respect to your obligations or otherwise relating to the business of the Company; (v) your material violation of any Company policy; (vi) your material breach of any agreement entered into between you and the Company; or (vii) your unauthorized use or disclosure of confidential information or trade secrets of the Company or its affiliates.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="RARE-EX1036_615_HTM__DV_C84">
</A>
<A NAME="RARE-EX1036_615_HTM__DV_M81">
</A>
<A NAME="RARE-EX1036_615_HTM_DV_M50">
</A>
<A NAME="RARE-EX1036_615_HTM__DV_M82">
</A>
	For the purposes of this letter, &#8220;Constructive Termination&#8221; means the occurrence of any of the following events without your written consent: (i) a material reduction or change in your job duties, responsibilities and requirements from your job duties, responsibilities and requirements immediately prior to such reduction or change, taking into account the differences in job title and duties that are normally occasioned by reason of an acquisition of one company by another; (ii) a material reduction of your Base Salary (other than an equal, across-the-board reduction in the compensation of all similarly-situated employees of the Company or the surviving entity that is approved by the B
<A NAME="RARE-EX1036_615_HTM__DV_C84">
</A>
	oard); or (iii) a requirement that you relocate to a principal office that increases your one-way commute by more than 50 miles relative to your immediately preceding principal office.&nbsp;&nbsp;Notwithstanding the foregoing, none of the foregoing events or conditions will constitute Constructive Termination unless: (x) you provide the Company with written objection (or notice) to the event or condition within 30 days following the occurrence thereof, (y) the Company does not reverse or otherwise cure the event or condition within
<A NAME="RARE-EX1036_615_HTM__DV_M81">
</A>
	30
<A NAME="RARE-EX1036_615_HTM_DV_M50">
</A>
<A NAME="RARE-EX1036_615_HTM__DV_M82">
</A>
	days of receiving that written objection, and (z) you resign your employment within 30 days following the expiration of that cure period.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Notwithstanding any other provision herein or any other plan, arrangement or agreement to the contrary, if any of the payments or benefits provided or to be provided by the Company or its affiliates to you or for your benefit pursuant to the terms of this Offer Letter or otherwise (&#8220;Covered Payments&#8221;) constitute parachute payments (&#8220;Parachute Payments&#8221;) within the meaning of Section 280G of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as amended (the &#8220;Code&#8221;) and would, but for this paragraph be subject to the excise tax imposed under Section 4999 of the Code (or any successor provision thereto) or any similar tax imposed by state or local law or any interest or penalties with respect to such taxes (collectively, the &#8220;Excise Tax&#8221;), then the Covered Payments shall be either (i) reduced to the minimum extent necessary to ensure that no portion of the Covered Payments is subject to the Excise Tax (that amount, the &#8220;Reduced Amount&#8221;) or (ii) payable in full if your receipt on an after-tax basis of the full amount of payments and benefits (after taking into account the applicable federal, state, local and foreign income, employment and excise taxes (including the Excise Tax)) would result in you receiving an amount greater than the Reduced Amount.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>

<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" ALIGN="CENTER" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; WIDTH:100%;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#9BBB59;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	www.ultragenyx.com
</P>

<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#7F7F7F;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">

<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage129"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="RARE-EX1036_615_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU6">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Any reduction pursuant to the preceding paragraph shall be made in a manner consistent with the requirements of Section 409A of the Code and the following: (i) the Covered Payments which do not constitute nonqualified deferred compensation subject to Section 409A of the Code shall be reduced first; and (ii) all other Covered Payments shall then be reduced as follows: (A) cash payments shall be reduced before non-cash payments; and (B) payments to be made on a later payment date shall be reduced before payments to be made on an earlier payment date.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Any such required determination shall be made in writing in good faith by an independent accounting firm selected by the Company (the &#8220;Accountants&#8221;), which shall provide detailed supporting calculations to the Company and you as reasonably requested by the Company or you. The Company and you shall provide the Accountants with such information and documents as the Accountants may reasonably request in order to make a determination. For purposes of making the calculations and determinations required herein, the Accountants may rely on reasonable, good faith assumptions and approximations concerning the application of Section 280G and Section 4999 of the Code. The Accountants&#8217; determinations shall be final and binding on the Company and you.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company shall be responsible for all fees and expenses incurred by the Accountants in connection with the calculations required herein.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;

<A NAME="eolPage130"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="RARE-EX1036_615_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU7">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Compliance with Section 409A
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="RARE-EX1036_615_HTM__DV_C62">
</A>
	It is intended that all of the severance benefits and other payments payable under this letter satisfy, to the greatest extent possible, the exemptions from the application of Code Section 409A provided under Treasury Regulations 1.409A&#8209;1(b)(4), 1.409A&#8209;1(b)(5) and 1.409A&#8209;1(b)(9), and this letter agreement will be construed to the greatest extent possible as consistent with those provisions, and to the extent not so exempt, this letter (and any definitions hereunder) will be construed in a manner that complies with Section 409A.&nbsp;&nbsp;Any payment by the Company under this letter agreement that is subject to Section 409A and that is contingent on a termination of employment is contingent on a &#8220;separation from service&#8221; within the meaning of Section 409A.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each such payment shall be considered to be a separate payment for purposes of Section 409A.&nbsp;&nbsp;Notwithstanding any provision to the contrary in this letter, if you are deemed by the Company at the time of your Separation from Service to be a &#8220;specified employee&#8221; for purposes of Code Section 409A(a)(2)(B)(i), and if any of the payments upon Separation from Service set forth herein and/or under any other agreement with the Company are deemed to be &#8220;deferred compensation&#8221;, then to the extent delayed commencement of any portion of such payments is required in order to avoid a prohibited distribution under Code Section 409A(a)(2)(B)(i) and the related adverse taxation under Section 409A, such payments shall not be provided to you prior to the earliest of (i) the expiration of the six-month period measured from the date of your Separation from Service with the Company, (ii) the date of your death, or (iii) such earlier date as permitted under Section 409A without the imposition of adverse taxation.&nbsp;&nbsp;Upon the first business day following the expiration of such applicable Code Section 409A(a)(2)(B)(i) period, all payments deferred pursuant to this paragraph shall be paid in a lump sum to you, and any remaining payments due shall be paid as otherwise provided herein or in the applicable agreement.&nbsp;&nbsp;No interest shall be due on any amounts so deferred.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Compliance with Company Policies
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	As an employee of the Company, you will be expected to comply with the Company&#8217;s personnel and other policies, including but not limited to, the Company&#8217;s policies prohibiting discrimination and unlawful harassment, conflicts of interest and violation of applicable laws in the course of performing services to the Company.&nbsp;&nbsp;During your orientation, you will be provided with the Company&#8217;s policy and procedures.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">

<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Full-time Services to the Company
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The Company requires that, as a full-time employee, you devote your full business time, attention, skills and efforts to the tasks and duties of your position as assigned by the Company.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, the Company will not preclude you from providing services to others, so long as such services would not be to the benefit of a competitor of the Company and will not otherwise interfere with your ability to satisfactorily fulfill your job responsibilities to the Company.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you wish to perform services (for any or no form of compensation) to any other person or business entity while employed by the Company, please contact the CEO and discuss your plans in advance of providing such services so that no problem later arises that could have been avoided from the outset.&nbsp;&nbsp;Any other such services must be approved by the CEO and Board.
</P>

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	This letter shall be interpreted in accordance with the laws of the State of California without giving effect to provisions governing the choice of law.&nbsp;&nbsp;If any provision of this letter becomes or is deemed invalid, illegal or unenforceable in any applicable jurisdiction by reason of the scope, extent or duration of its coverage, then such provision shall be deemed amended to the minimum extent necessary to conform to applicable law so as to be valid and enforceable or, if such provision cannot be so amended without materially altering the intention of the parties, then such provision shall be stricken and the remainder of this letter shall continue in full force and effect.&nbsp;&nbsp;If any provision of this letter is rendered illegal by any present or future statute, law, ordinance or regulation (collectively, the &#8220;Law&#8221;) then that provision shall be curtailed or limited only to the minimum extent necessary to bring the provision into compliance with the Law.&nbsp;&nbsp;All the other terms and provisions of this letter shall continue in full force and effect without impairment or limitation.
</P>

	I accept the above offer:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;

<EFX_EXHIBIT_10>
<A NAME="FIS_EXHIBIT_10_4"></A>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Exhibit 10.37
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6PT;MARGIN-TOP:6PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<IMG SRC="http://content.edgar-online.com/edgar_conv_img/2017/02/17/0001564590-17-001714_G2017021622363996110270.JPG" TITLE="" ALT="" STYLE="WIDTH:194PX;HEIGHT:74PX;">
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	June 11, 2015
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	John Pinion
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.77%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Re: Offer of Employment
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Dear John,
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	On behalf of Ultragenyx Pharmaceutical Inc. (the &#8220;Company&#8221;), I am pleased to present to you an offer of full-time employment as Chief Quality Operations Officer/Senior Vice President, Analytical Sciences and Research.&#160; The Company&#8217;s Board of Directors (the &#8220;Board&#8221;) and I are excited about the important contributions you can make by joining the Ultragenyx leadership team and are confident that you will play a key role in our company's growth and success.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	In your role as Chief Quality Operations Officer, you will report directly to me and be a member of the Executive Leadership Team (XLT).&#160; In this role, you will provide the leadership, strategic vision, and functional expertise required to lead the Company to successful commercialization of its products for rare and ultra-rare diseases on a global basis.&nbsp;&nbsp;You will provide direction for the overall quality operations, including QA GxP, Compliance, Validation, QC GMP, QC Clinical and QC Research, in the achievement of its short-term and long range business objectives.&nbsp;&nbsp;As for all functions at Ultragenyx, the quality group is expected to work in an integrated fashion with technical operations, development, program management, translational research, and business development to drive the growth and success of the company. This includes establishing, maintaining and evolving the critical and unique strategies for development at Ultragenyx which depend on close collaborations between departments, and novel approaches to traditional clinical development challenges.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	You will also have the opportunity to participate as an executive member of the Translational Research Management team and lead an early development program.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, you will serve on the Business Development Review forum that will allow you to be in involved in diligence planning and review, reviewing IP issues, reviewing license and deal terms and strategies on collaboration agreements.&nbsp;&nbsp;Given our growth, the XLT will also be managing the operational details for a growing company and making critical decisions&nbsp;&nbsp;on how best to set up the company for success to support the business and create a work environment so employees can thrive.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Compensation
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="RARE-EX1037_613_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU2">
</A>
	In the regular exempt position of Chief Quality Operations Officer, the Company shall pay you as compensation for your services an initial base salary at a gross annual rate of $390,000 (the
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:6PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<DIV ALIGN="LEFT">
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; WIDTH:100%;">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:25.24%;">
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:41.74%;">
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:33.02%;">
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#9BBB59;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	www.ultragenyx.com
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#7F7F7F;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Turning good science into great medicine
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#7F7F7F;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	1
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage135"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#8220;Base Salary&#8221;).&nbsp;&nbsp;Such Base Salary shall be payable in accordance with the Company&#8217;s standard payroll procedures and subject to standard payroll deductions and withholdings.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Board or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Compensation Committee of the Board shall review your Base Salary at least annually.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	In addition to your Base Salary, pursuant to the Company&#8217;s corporate bonus plan (or such other incentive plan maintained by the Company) you will be eligible to earn an annual bonus of up to 40% of your Base Salary based upon your performance during the previous year as evaluated by the CEO in consultation with the Board (or Compensation Committee of the Board) against pre-determined individual and/or corporate performance goals.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Equity Grants
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Subject to the approval of the Compensation Committee, you will receive an option to purchase up to an aggregate of 90,000 shares of the Company&#8217;s Common Stock (the &#8220;Option&#8221;) pursuant to the Company&#8217;s 2014 Incentive Plan (the &#8220;Plan&#8221;). The exercise price of the Option will be equal to the closing price per share of Common Stock on the date of grant.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The Option will vest and become exercisable as follows: 1/4
<SUP STYLE="FONT-SIZE:85%; VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
	th
</SUP>
	of the shares initially subject to the Option shall vest and become exercisable on the first (1
<SUP STYLE="FONT-SIZE:85%; VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
	st
</SUP>
	) anniversary of the first day of your employment with the Company, and thereafter 1/48
<SUP STYLE="FONT-SIZE:85%; VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
	th
</SUP>
	of the shares initially subject to the Option shall vest and become exercisable each month until the Option is fully vested, in each case subject to your continued employment by the Company (or its subsidiaries).&nbsp;&nbsp;The Option shall be governed by the Company&#8217;s standard form of stock option agreements and the Plan.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Subject to the approval of the Compensation Committee, you will also receive a grant of 7,500 restricted stock units (the &#8220;RSUs&#8221;) pursuant to the Plan.&#160; The RSUs will vest annually over a four-year period from the date of grant (i.e., 25% of the RSUs shall vest and become exercisable on each anniversary of the first day of your employment with the Company during the four-year period), in each case subject to your continued employment by the Company (or its consolidated subsidiaries).&#160; The RSUs shall be governed by the Company&#8217;s standard form of restricted stock unit agreement and the Plan.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Notwithstanding the foregoing, in the event that (i) the Company consummates a Covered Transaction (as defined in the Plan), (ii) on the date such Covered Transaction is consummated you are employed by the Company (or its subsidiaries) and (iii) within 12 months after the date such Covered Transaction is consummated your employment by the Company (or its successor or subsidiaries) is terminated without Cause (as defined below) or you resign such employment due to a Constructive Termination (as defined below),
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;">
	then provided such termination constitutes a &#8220;separation from service&#8221; (as defined under Treasury Regulation Section 1.409A-1(h), without regard to any alternative definition thereunder, a &#8220;Separation from Service&#8221;),
</FONT>
	in addition to the severance benefits set forth below, the vesting of any equity-based compensation awards granted to you in connection with your employment shall accelerate with respect to 100% of the then-unvested shares then subject to such awards.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:6PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>

	www.ultragenyx.com
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">

</A>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Benefits
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	You will be eligible to participate in all of the employee benefits and benefit plans that the Company generally makes available to its full-time regular employees, subject to the terms and conditions of such benefits and benefit plans.&nbsp;&nbsp;At this time, these will include at a minimum, medical, dental and vision insurance coverage. Coverage for these benefits begins on the 1
<SUP STYLE="FONT-SIZE:85%; VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
	st
</SUP>
	day of the month following your first day of employment with the Company. Detailed information about the benefits presently available will be provided to you on your first day of employment.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The health plan options will include 4 medical plans (2-HMO, PPO and HSA), a dental and vision plan, life/AD&amp;D insurance, disability and voluntary insurance as well as a 401(k) retirement plan, with a company match of 3%.&#160; The Company will cover 90% of the employee benefit costs and 75% of the dependent benefits costs.&#160; Based on conditions and situations over time, the Company may change specific benefits and plans from time to time, but our intent is to provide an excellent health benefit program to our employees.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	You will accrue vacation time at the rate of four weeks (160 hours) per year, up to an accrual cap of 240 hours, under the terms of the Company&#8217;s PTO policy.&#160; You will also be eligible for 5 sick days.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	&#8220;At Will&#8221; Employment
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Employment with the Company is &#8220;at-will&#8221;.&nbsp;&nbsp;This means that it is not for any specified period of time and can be terminated by you or by the Company at any time, with or without advance notice, and for any or no particular reason or Cause.&nbsp;&nbsp;It also means that your job duties, title, responsibilities, reporting level, compensation and benefits, as well as the Company&#8217;s personnel policies and procedures, may be changed at any time, with or without notice in the sole discretion of the Company.&nbsp;&nbsp;This &#8220;at-will&#8221; nature of your employment shall remain unchanged during your tenure as an employee, and can only be changed by an express written agreement that is signed by you and by the Company&#8217;s CEO.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:6PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>

	www.ultragenyx.com
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#7F7F7F;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">

	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="RARE-EX1037_613_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU4">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Severance
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	If, at any time, your employment with the Company or its successor is terminated without Cause, or you resign your employment due to a Constructive Termination, then provided such termination constitutes a Separation from Service, the Company shall: (i) extend the exercise period applicable to the Option (and to any other options to purchase the Company&#8217;s Common Stock you then hold) such that you will have until the date that is twelve (12) months after the date of your Separation from Service to exercise any of the vested shares (determined as of the date of your Separation from Service) subject to the Option (but in no event will the exercise period be extended until later than the date of expiration of the term of the Option as set forth in the agreement evidencing such Option); and (ii) the Company shall pay you, as severance, the equivalent of one (1) year of your Base Salary in effect as of the date of your Separation from Service, subject to standard payroll deductions and withholdings (the &#8220;Severance Amount&#8221;).&nbsp;&nbsp;The Severance Amount will be paid in installments in the form of continuation of your Base Salary payments, paid on the Company&#8217;s regular payroll dates, commencing on the Company&#8217;s first regular payroll date that follows the 60th day after such Separation from Service.&nbsp;&nbsp;The first regular payroll date that follows the 60
<SUP STYLE="FONT-SIZE:85%; VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
	th
</SUP>
	day after such Separation from Service shall be for all accrued Base Salary for the 60-day period plus the period from the 60
<SUP STYLE="FONT-SIZE:85%; VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
	th
</SUP>
	day until the regular payroll date; the remainder of the Base Salary continuation payments shall thereafter be made on the Company&#8217;s regular payroll dates.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Notwithstanding anything herein to the contrary, the receipt of any of the severance or acceleration benefits described in this letter will be subject to and conditioned upon: (i) your signing a separation agreement and release of claims in a form reasonably satisfactory to the Company (the &#8220;Separation Agreement&#8221;) and such Separation Agreement becoming effective and irrevocable as specified therein no later than sixty (60) days following your Separation from Service; and (ii) your continued compliance with the terms of this letter, the Separation Agreement, the enclosed Confidential Information and Invention Assignment Agreement (including without limitation, your not using or disclosing any confidential or proprietary information of the Company), and any other agreement entered into between you and the Company.&nbsp;&nbsp;No severance benefits of any kind will be paid or provided, and no acceleration of vesting shall be effective, until the Separation Agreement becomes effective.&nbsp;&nbsp;You shall also resign from all positions and terminate any relationships as an employee, advisor, officer or director with the Company and any of its affiliates, each effective on the date of termination.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Additionally, and for the avoidance of doubt, in the event that the Company terminates your employment for Cause, or you resign your employment for any reason other than due to a Constructive Termination, or your employment terminates upon your death or disability, you will no longer vest in the Option or the RSUs (or any other equity) and you will not be entitled to any severance benefits described herein.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:6PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#7F7F7F;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">

<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage138"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="RARE-EX1037_613_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU5">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	For purposes of this offer letter, &#8220;Cause&#8221; means any of the following: (i) your gross negligence in carrying out, or material failure to carry out, your duties for the Company (including without limitation, your failure to cooperate in any Company investigation), after notice from the Board and a reasonable opportunity to cure (if deemed curable); (ii) any breach of your fiduciary duties to the Company, after notice from the Board and a reasonable opportunity to cure (if deemed curable); (iii) conviction of, or plea of guilty or no contest to, any felony; (iv) any act of fraud or embezzlement by you with respect to your obligations or otherwise relating to the business of the Company; (v) your material violation of any Company policy; (vi) your material breach of any agreement entered into between you and the Company; or (vii) your unauthorized use or disclosure of confidential information or trade secrets of the Company or its affiliates.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;COLOR:#000000;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="RARE-EX1037_613_HTM__DV_C84">
</A>
<A NAME="RARE-EX1037_613_HTM__DV_M81">
</A>
<A NAME="RARE-EX1037_613_HTM_DV_M50">
</A>
<A NAME="RARE-EX1037_613_HTM__DV_M82">
</A>
	For the purposes of this letter, &#8220;Constructive Termination&#8221; means the occurrence of any of the following events without your written consent: (i) a material reduction or change in your job duties, responsibilities and requirements from your job duties, responsibilities and requirements immediately prior to such reduction or change, taking into account the differences in job title and duties that are normally occasioned by reason of an acquisition of one company by another; (ii) a material reduction of your Base Salary (other than an equal, across-the-board reduction in the compensation of all similarly-situated employees of the Company or the surviving entity that is approved by the B
<A NAME="RARE-EX1037_613_HTM__DV_C84">
</A>
	oard); or (iii) a requirement that you relocate to a principal office that increases your one-way commute by more than 50 miles relative to your immediately preceding principal office.&nbsp;&nbsp;Notwithstanding the foregoing, none of the foregoing events or conditions will constitute Constructive Termination unless: (x) you provide the Company with written objection (or notice) to the event or condition within 30 days following the occurrence thereof, (y) the Company does not reverse or otherwise cure the event or condition within
<A NAME="RARE-EX1037_613_HTM__DV_M81">
</A>
	30
<A NAME="RARE-EX1037_613_HTM_DV_M50">
</A>
<A NAME="RARE-EX1037_613_HTM__DV_M82">
</A>
	days of receiving that written objection, and (z) you resign your employment within 30 days following the expiration of that cure period.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Notwithstanding any other provision herein or any other plan, arrangement or agreement to the contrary, if any of the payments or benefits provided or to be provided by the Company or its affiliates to you or for your benefit pursuant to the terms of this Offer Letter or otherwise (&#8220;Covered Payments&#8221;) constitute parachute payments (&#8220;Parachute Payments&#8221;) within the meaning of Section 280G of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as amended (the &#8220;Code&#8221;) and would, but for this paragraph be subject to the excise tax imposed under Section 4999 of the Code (or any successor provision thereto) or any similar tax imposed by state or local law or any interest or penalties with respect to such taxes (collectively, the &#8220;Excise Tax&#8221;), then the Covered Payments shall be either (i) reduced to the minimum extent necessary to ensure that no portion of the Covered Payments is subject to the Excise Tax (that amount, the &#8220;Reduced Amount&#8221;) or (ii) payable in full if your receipt on an after-tax basis of the full amount of payments and benefits (after taking into account the applicable federal, state, local and foreign income, employment and excise taxes (including the Excise Tax)) would result in you receiving an amount greater than the Reduced Amount.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:6PT;">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="RARE-EX1037_613_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU6">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Any reduction pursuant to the preceding paragraph shall be made in a manner consistent with the requirements of Section 409A of the Code and the following: (i) the Covered Payments which do not constitute nonqualified deferred compensation subject to Section 409A of the Code shall be reduced first; and (ii) all other Covered Payments shall then be reduced as follows: (A) cash payments shall be reduced before non-cash payments; and (B) payments to be made on a later payment date shall be reduced before payments to be made on an earlier payment date.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Any such required determination shall be made in writing in good faith by an independent accounting firm selected by the Company (the &#8220;Accountants&#8221;), which shall provide detailed supporting calculations to the Company and you as reasonably requested by the Company or you. The Company and you shall provide the Accountants with such information and documents as the Accountants may reasonably request in order to make a determination. For purposes of making the calculations and determinations required herein, the Accountants may rely on reasonable, good faith assumptions and approximations concerning the application of Section 280G and Section 4999 of the Code. The Accountants&#8217; determinations shall be final and binding on the Company and you.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company shall be responsible for all fees and expenses incurred by the Accountants in connection with the calculations required herein.
</P>

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="RARE-EX1037_613_HTM__DV_C62">
</A>
	It is intended that all of the severance benefits and other payments payable under this letter satisfy, to the greatest extent possible, the exemptions from the application of Code Section 409A provided under Treasury Regulations 1.409A&#8209;1(b)(4), 1.409A&#8209;1(b)(5) and 1.409A&#8209;1(b)(9), and this letter agreement will be construed to the greatest extent possible as consistent with those provisions, and to the extent not so exempt, this letter (and any definitions hereunder) will be construed in a manner that complies with Section 409A.&nbsp;&nbsp;Any payment by the Company under this letter agreement that is subject to Section 409A and that is contingent on a termination of employment is contingent on a &#8220;separation from service&#8221; within the meaning of Section 409A.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each such payment shall be considered to be a separate payment for purposes of Section 409A.&nbsp;&nbsp;Notwithstanding any provision to the contrary in this letter, if you are deemed by the Company at the time of your Separation from Service to be a &#8220;specified employee&#8221; for purposes of Code Section 409A(a)(2)(B)(i), and if any of the payments upon Separation from Service set forth herein and/or under any other agreement with the Company are deemed to be &#8220;deferred compensation&#8221;, then to the extent delayed commencement of any portion of such payments is required in order to avoid a prohibited distribution under Code Section 409A(a)(2)(B)(i) and the related adverse taxation under Section 409A, such payments shall not be provided to you prior to the earliest of (i) the expiration of the six-month period measured from the date of your Separation from Service with the Company, (ii) the date of your death, or (iii) such earlier date as permitted under Section 409A without the imposition of adverse taxation.&nbsp;&nbsp;Upon the first business day following the expiration of such applicable Code Section 409A(a)(2)(B)(i) period, all payments deferred pursuant to this paragraph shall be paid in a lump sum to you, and any remaining payments due shall be paid as otherwise provided herein or in the applicable agreement.&nbsp;&nbsp;No interest shall be due on any amounts so deferred.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Compliance with Company Policies
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;

	As an employee of the Company, you will be expected to comply with the Company&#8217;s personnel and other policies, including but not limited to, the Company&#8217;s policies prohibiting discrimination and unlawful harassment, conflicts of interest and violation of applicable laws in the course of performing services to the Company.&nbsp;&nbsp;During your orientation, you will be provided with the Company&#8217;s policy and procedures.

<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">

</FONT>

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">

<A NAME="RARE-EX1037_613_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU8">

	The Company requires that, as a full-time employee, you devote your full business time, attention, skills and efforts to the tasks and duties of your position as assigned by the Company.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, the Company will not preclude you from providing services to others, so long as such services would not be to the benefit of a competitor of the Company and will not otherwise interfere with your ability to satisfactorily fulfill your job responsibilities to the Company.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you wish to perform services (for any or no form of compensation) to any other

	If you accept this offer, and the conditions of this offer are satisfied, this letter and the written agreements referenced in this letter shall constitute the complete agreement between you and the Company with respect to the initial terms and conditions of your employment.&nbsp;&nbsp;Any representations, promises or agreements, whether written or oral, not contained in this letter or contrary to those contained in this letter, that may have been made to you are expressly cancelled and replaced by this offer letter.&nbsp;&nbsp; Except as otherwise specified in this letter or in the written agreements referenced in this letter, the terms and conditions of your employment pursuant to this letter may not be changed, except by a writing issued by the CEO with approval by the Board.

	We look forward to you accepting this offer and a mutually rewarding relationship.&nbsp;&nbsp;As with all important decisions, you should make a decision concerning this offer based on your own investigation and judgment concerning the Company and its prospects, independent of the opinions and perspectives that may have been shared with you by any Company employee.

	If you accept this offer, please date and sign below, on the enclosed copy of this letter and return it to me no later than June 30, 2015.&nbsp;&nbsp;Please retain the original of this letter for your records.&nbsp;&nbsp; You should bring your INS Form I-9 required identification and proof of authorization to work with you on your first day of employment.

</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	We look forward to working with you on developing treatment for many rare genetic diseases and hope you find your employment at Ultragenyx Pharmaceutical a rewarding experience.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you have any questions regarding this offer letter, please feel free to contact me at (415) 483-XXXX.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">

<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	April 27, 2015
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFFF;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Jayson Dallas
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.77%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Re: Offer of Employment
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Dear Jayson,
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.77%;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	On behalf of Ultragenyx Pharmaceutical Inc. (the &#8220;Company&#8221;), I am pleased to present to you an offer of full-time employment as Chief Commercial Officer.&#160; The Company&#8217;s Board of Directors (the &#8220;Board&#8221;) and I are excited about the important contributions you can make by joining the Ultragenyx management team and are confident that you will play a key role in our company's growth and success.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	In your role as Chief Commercial Officer, you will report directly to me and be a member of the Executive Leadership Team.&#160; In this role, you will provide the leadership, strategic vision, and functional expertise required to lead the Company to successful commercialization of its products for rare and ultra-rare diseases on a global basis.&nbsp;&nbsp;You will provide direction for the overall commercial operations, including sales leadership, marketing, managed care, commercial analytics, forecasting, and new product planning in building and leading a best-in-class biopharmaceutical commercial organization in the achievement of its short-term and long range business objectives.&nbsp;&nbsp;As for all functions at Ultragenyx, the commercial group is expected to work in an integrated fashion with development, program management, technical operations, and business development to drive the growth and success of the company. This includes establishing, maintaining and evolving the critical and unique strategies for development at Ultragenyx which depend on close collaborations between departments, and novel approaches to traditional clinical development challenges.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<DIV ALIGN="LEFT">
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; WIDTH:100%;">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:28.48%;">
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:54.37%;">
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:17.15%;">
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#9BBB59;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	www.ultragenyx.com
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#7F7F7F;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Turning good science into great medicine
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0PT;;TEXT-INDENT:0PT;;COLOR:#7F7F7F;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-SIZE:11PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	1
</P>
</TD>

<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage145"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="RARE-EX1038_612_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU2">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Compensation
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	In the regular exempt position of Chief Commercial Officer, the Company shall pay you as compensation for your services an initial base salary at a gross annual rate of $425,000 (the &#8220;Base Salary&#8221;).&nbsp;&nbsp;Such Base Salary shall be payable in accordance with the Company&#8217;s standard payroll procedures and subject to standard payroll deductions and withholdings.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Board or the Compensation Committee of the Board shall review your Base Salary at least annually.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	In addition to your Base Salary, pursuant to the Company&#8217;s corporate bonus plan (or such other incentive plan maintained by the Company) you will be eligible to earn an annual bonus of up to 40% of your Base Salary based upon your performance during the previous year as evaluated by the CEO in consultation with the Board (or Compensation Committee of the Board) against pre-determined individual and/or corporate performance goals.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, the Company will provide you with a sign-on bonus in the amount of $100,000, subject to applicable federal and state taxes, to be paid within 30 days of your start date.&nbsp;&nbsp;In the event that you should voluntarily terminate your employment with Ultragenyx, or are terminated for &#8220;cause&#8221;, within twelve (12) months of your hire date, you shall, no later than the effective date of such termination, refund to the Company the full amount of such bonus payment paid by the Company.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Employee further agrees to pay all costs reasonably incurred by Ultragenyx in connection with the collection of such refund, including reasonable attorney&#8217;s fees.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The Company will also provide you with a retention bonus in the amount of $100,000 to be paid in two installments, with the first installment to be paid on the 1
<SUP STYLE="FONT-SIZE:85%; VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
	st
</SUP>
	anniversary of the first day of your employment with the Company and the second installment to be paid on the 2
<SUP STYLE="FONT-SIZE:85%; VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
	nd
</SUP>
	anniversary of the first day of your employment with the Company.&nbsp;&nbsp;In order to receive any bonus payment, you must be continuously employed through, and still employed by the Company on the date any such bonus is paid.&nbsp;&nbsp;Any such bonus shall be payable no later than March 15th following the end of such applicable fiscal period in which such bonus is earned.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Equity Grants
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Subject to the approval of the Compensation Committee, you will receive an option to purchase up to an aggregate of 75,000 shares of the Company&#8217;s Common Stock (the &#8220;Option&#8221;) pursuant to the Company&#8217;s 2014 Incentive Plan (the &#8220;Plan&#8221;). The exercise price of the Option will be equal to the closing price per share of Common Stock on the date of grant.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:CALIBRI;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The Option will vest and become exercisable as follows: 1/4
<SUP STYLE="FONT-SIZE:85%; VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
	th
</SUP>
	of the shares initially subject to the Option shall vest and become exercisable on the first (1
<SUP STYLE="FONT-SIZE:85%; VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
	st
</SUP>
	) anniversary of the first day of your employment with the Company, and thereafter 1/48
<SUP STYLE="FONT-SIZE:85%; VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
	th
</SUP>
	of the shares initially subject to the Option shall vest and become exercisable each month until the Option is fully vested, in each case subject to your continued employment by the Company (or its subsidiaries).&nbsp;&nbsp;The Option shall be governed by the Company&#8217;s standard form of stock option agreements and the Plan.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;

	&nbsp;
